三、課程大綱 Syllabus (本課程大綱教師得依實際教學進度及學生學習情況進行調整)


■  課程目標及內涵 (Course Objectives and Contents)The objective of this course is to introduce basic concepts for stochastic processes. The main focus will be on studying analytical models for systems which change states stochastically with time.  The topics include: Poisson processes, discrete-time Markov chains, continuous-time Markov chains, renewal processes, Brownian motion, etc.(1) Poisson process (basic definitions and properties), (2) nonhomogeneous Poisson processes (properties and applications), (3) discrete-time Markov chains (classification of states, periodicity, ergodic, finite-state Markov chain), (4) hidden Markov models, (5) continuous-time Markov chains (Chapman-Kolmogorov equations, infinitesimal generator, birth and death Processes), (6) Brownian motion (properties, Black-Scholes formula)


■  多元教學方式 (Muliti-Teaching Methods)說明：除了課堂講授與考試測驗之外，本課程在學期中可能會運用到以下哪些教學方式，以期能進一步提升學生學習成效
        


■  主要參考書籍/資料 (Textbooks and References)
    (教科書遵守智慧財產權觀念不得非法影印)1. Sheldon M. Ross (2014) Introduction to Probability Models, 11th ed, Academic Press
2. Sheldon M. Ross (1996) Stochastic Processes, 2nd ed, John Wiley , New York.    


